parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake drops to the floorboard
the parking brake fails to engage
the parking brake is difficult to apply.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the rear brakes detach from the vehicle
the rear brakes fail after driving over bumpy terrain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The front brake rotors warp quickly
the vehicle shimmies or vibrates when braking
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS system works intermittently
the brakes pulsate or vibrate
the ABS light comes on
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Air in Hydraulic System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air in the hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail suddenly
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake line rusts through and bursts
the brakes fail suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective brake components can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake rotors
pads
or calipers are defective
the brakes fail suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transfer Case Failure (ESOF/Touch Drive Electric Shift 4X4)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power and momentum, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle will suddenly act like it is no longer in gear
the vehicle will not respond to acceleration
the transfer case slips out of 4x4 gear
the vehicle will stall unexpectedly
the differential falls into neutral
the vehicle will roll or move without engine braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and momentum, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The transmission fails
overdrive turns on/off
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the vehicle will stall unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise
sudden loss of air pressure
vibration
and loss of control while driving
often at high speeds.
